post_text:
Good Evening Justice Families.

Although we are virtual this Thursday and Friday, we will be serving grab-n-go meals on Thursday from 9:30-11:30am for all Justice students only. Thursday's pick-up will have meals for both Thursday and Friday of this week.

We will be blended virtual starting next Monday. We will still serve grab-n-go meals daily from 9:30-11:30 for virtual students. We will serve the blended virtual students meals in the cafeteria when they are on campus. We will have a modified meal schedule in order to meet social distancing and cleaning and disinfecting between small groups.

We miss all our Warriors! We are hoping that everyone continues to practice safe behaviors so that our local numbers can drop us to a safer category for returning to school in a more traditionalsetting. Until then, be safe and your teachers will be calling regularly.

Warriors Forever!

post_text:
State schools Superintendent Joy Hofmeister said today that Oklahoma’s public school students should not return to their physical classrooms for the remainder of the school year. Instead, she’ll ask the state Board of Education on Wednesday to waive instructional day and year requirements and allow school districts to serve students remotely beginning April 6.

If approved, school districts could now begin virtually convening teachers to plan for the remote reopening of school. State education officials said the state board is expected to lift the part of its previous order that prohibited teacher professional development.
text:
State schools Superintendent Joy Hofmeister said today that Oklahoma’s public school students should not return to their physical classrooms for the remainder of the school year. Instead, she’ll ask the state Board of Education on Wednesday to waive instructional day and year requirements and allow school districts to serve students remotely beginning April 6.

If approved, school districts could now begin virtually convening teachers to plan for the remote reopening of school. State education officials said the state board is expected to lift the part of its previous order that prohibited teacher professional development.

post_text: A message from Mrs. Dorothy Gilleland-Ray to her students.
shared_text:
Dorothy Gilleland-Ray
March 23 at 4:23 PM ·

To my class of 2019/2020,
I love you. I miss you. If I'd known we wouldn't be coming back together for the school year, I would have said more and hugged you tighter. I am proud of each and every one of you. You have made tremendous progress and should be proud of yourselves. If there is something you left behind, I promise, it will be there when this mess is over. I will always be here to support you, help you, and cheer you on. You are in my thoughts daily and my prayers nightly. Keep your chins up, stay healthy, and remember that Mrs. Ray enjoyed having you in her classroom. 💔

*Mr.Bryan and Mr. Jones , if its possible to put this on our website so that my kids know I am thinking of them, I'd appreciate it, as I am not Facebook friends with students or their parents.

If you did NOT submit a survey for our projected meal count at, please message he school through Facebook or leave a message at 405-257-2962 x3403 (Mrs. Sherrin) or x3404 (Mr. Bryan). School staff will be on hand to deliver meals to vehicles as they pull through the circle drive. We will have both the superintendent and principal’s administrative offices open and manned with their regular personnel from 8-1 daily. Thank you and be safe.

post_text:
Good Evening Warrior Nation!

It is with a heavy heart that I am posting an update on the loss of our colleague, teacher, bus driver, and most of all...friend. Services for Mrs. Tonya Knapp are still pending at this time. Regular classes will resume tomorrow. We will hold an assembly at 8:00 a.m. in the Field House for all students. We encourage and welcome any and all parents and guardians to join us. We will have counselors and a wealth of people on site and available to talk with students, staff, and parents. This resource will be available next week as well. We will travel the road of grief together. This is a teachable moment for us all as everyone grieves differently, whether it is crying, silence, anger, laughing at the memory of special moments, etc. We have activities scheduled to help us return to a somewhat normal routine. Please remember the Knapp family in your thoughts and prayers. We will be posting more information as it becomes available.

Faithfully,
Chris Bryan
